TITLE: Joe Biden takes Hunter to Camp David two weekends in a row amid scandal
SUMMARY: President Biden traveled with Hunter Biden to Camp David for the second weekend in a row Friday, just days after the DOJ announced a tentative plea agreement for the first son.

TITLE: Obama's AG weighs in on whether Biden should pardon Trump
SUMMARY: Former Attorney General Eric Holder joined CBS News' "Face the Nation" and discussed if President Biden or the 2024 White House winner should potentially pardon Donald Trump.

TITLE: Biden to meet with King Charles and UK PM Rishi Sunak ahead of NATO summit, White House announces
SUMMARY: President Biden is scheduled to meet with King Charles and U.K. Prime Minister Rishi Sunak to "further strengthen" the countries' relationship before attending the NATO summit.

TITLE: New laws: Here are some of the most impactful bills that took effect across the US on July 1
SUMMARY: From limits on abortion and transgender services to sealing criminal records in California, several major pieces of legislation went into effect on July 1.

TITLE: AOC proposes subpoenas and impeachment to limit SCOTUS justices’ power following landmark decisions
SUMMARY: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez reacted to the Supreme Court's landmark decisions this past week, proposing impeachment, subpoeanas and investigations to limit the justices' power.

TITLE: Biden slammed after report reveals number of grandchildren his aides instructed to say publicly: 'Monsters'
SUMMARY: White House aides have been told in strategy meetings that President Biden and the first lady only have six grandchildren, not seven, according to a new report.

TITLE: Nikki Haley sounds the alarm on China's military growth, blasts Pentagon for 'gender pronoun classes'
SUMMARY: Republican presidential candidate Nikki Haley is warning that the U.S. needs to take China's military threat seriously as they are "preparing for war."

TITLE: Independence Day: Fourth of July facts you may not know
SUMMARY: Each year, Americans celebrate the Fourth of July. The occasion is in honor of the adoption of the Declaration of Independence by Congress.

TITLE: Maryland law allowing recreational marijuana takes effect
SUMMARY: Recreational marijuana use in Maryland became legal for adults on Saturday after Governor Wes Moore signed the Cannabis Reform Act into law in May.

TITLE: Record-high number of 40-year-olds in US have never been married, study finds
SUMMARY: A record number of 40-year-olds in the United States have never been married, and most of them are living alone, according to a new analysis of U.S. Census Bureau data.

TITLE: Meet the Republican governor in demand with GOP presidential candidates — other than Trump
SUMMARY: Other than Donald Trump, all the other Republican presidential candidates are asking advice of New Hampshire Gov. Chris Sununu and would love to land his endorsement in the 2024 primary

TITLE: Trump ally Lindsey Graham booed off stage at South Carolina MAGA rally near his hometown
SUMMARY: Sen. Lindsey Graham faced an onslaught of booing as he stumped for former President Donald Trump at a rally in his home state of South Carolina on Saturday.

TITLE: Gorsuch and Sotomayor's clash in gay wedding opinion follows previous skirmish in praying coach ruling
SUMMARY: Supreme Court Justices Neil Gorsuch and Sonia Sotomayor are again at odds over a case concerning the First Amendment, with one accusing the other of "re-imagining" the facts.

TITLE: Chris Christie says he's 'living rent free' in Trump's head after former president shared photo of him asleep
SUMMARY: Formey New Jersey governor and Republican presidential candidate Chris Christie said Friday that he’s “living rent free in Donald’s head" after former President Donald Trump shared a photo of him sleeping on a plane.

TITLE: DeSantis campaign attacks Trump with Pride Month Twitter video
SUMMARY: The campaign of Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis – a 2024 GOP challenger battling former President Donald Trump – shared a video Friday hitting at Trump over his positions on LGBTQIA+ issues.

TITLE: US attorney leading Hunter Biden probe breaks silence on claims investigation was 'influenced by politics'
SUMMARY: The U.S. attorney handling the Hunter Biden investigation speaks out on whistleblower allegations against him and his prosecutorial decisions.

TITLE: Georgia parents of transgender children challenge state's ban on sex reassignment surgery for minors
SUMMARY: Parents of four transgender children filed a lawsuit against a Georgia law banning most sex reassignment surgeries and hormone replacement therapies for minors.

TITLE: Trump takes aim at 'crooked' Biden student loan plan after Supreme Court decision: 'Trying to buy votes'
SUMMARY: Former President Trump accused Biden of "trying to buy votes" during a Friday speech in Philadelphia, after Biden's student loan forgiveness plan was overruled by the Supreme Court.

TITLE: Hunter Biden's lawyer explodes at Ways and Means Committee for 'obsession' with DOJ investigation
SUMMARY: Hunter Biden’s attorney Abbe Lowell wrote an explosive letter to Rep. Jason Smith, R-Mo., on Friday, accusing the House Ways and Means Committee of disregarding rules of conduct.

TITLE: Texas Rep Wesley Hunt challenges 'woke' corporations with 'American Pride Month' legislation
SUMMARY: Rep. Wesley Hunt, R-Texas, introduced a resolution on Friday that would designate the month of July as "American Pride Month" and is encouraging Americans to be proud of their country.

TITLE: Footnote in Supreme Court’s affirmative action ruling excludes military academies
SUMMARY: A footnote in the Supreme Court majority opinion striking down affirmative action says military academies are exempt due to "potentially distinct interests" they present.

TITLE: Roberts scolds liberal justices for demonizing rulings they don't like: 'Disturbing feature' of dissents
SUMMARY: Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts scolded liberal justices for a "disturbing feature" in dissents that could mislead the public about the court's legitimacy.

TITLE: RFK blames Supreme Court student loan handout smackdown on Biden's 'failure'
SUMMARY: Robert Kennedy, Jr. said Friday President Biden's “failure" to unite Congress led to the “predictable" Supreme Court decision to strike down the president's student loan forgiveness.

TITLE: GOP presidential candidates spar over calls to impeach Biden for alleged meddling in Hunter investigation
SUMMARY: Two GOP presidential candidates bumped heads over a possible congressional investigation into whistleblower claims of meddling in the Hunter Biden probe.

TITLE: NY Democrat complains about her student debt after SCOTUS ruling, gets slammed for million dollar home
SUMMARY: Former New York state Democrat Sen. Alessandra Biaggi, despite purchasing a $1.14 million home last summer, said Friday that she still owes more than $200K in student loans from law school.
